Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Roast the pepper on a non-stick baking tray for ten minutes or until it starts to soften.Place the couscous in a heatproof bowl and pour over the hot stock.  Cover with a plate and leave to stand for five minutes.Remove the plate and fluff the couscous up with a fork.Add the lemon juice and olive oil and season well.Stir through the raisins, coriander and feta cheese then stuff the pepper halves with the couscous. Serve warm or cold.